        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix media completion duplicate delivery",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Reuse the active session transcript write lock for transcript appends so media completion wakeups do not self-contend with session-locked writes.\n- Make media generation duplicate guards distinguish active work from exact recent-success retries using stable request keys for image, video, and music tools.\n- Keep generated-media tasks active through completion delivery, fail them if delivery cannot be confirmed, and use direct generated-media delivery as a fallback for message-tool-only routes.\n- Add regression coverage for active/recent duplicate guards, completion delivery ordering, direct media fallback, task registry freshness, and transcript lock reuse.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/subagent-announce-delivery.test.ts src/agents/image-generation-task-status.test.ts src/agents/video-generation-task-status.test.ts src/agents/tools/image-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-tool.status.test.ts src/agents/tools/music-generate-tool.status.test.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/music-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/image-generate-background.test.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-background.test.ts src/agents/tools/music-generate-background.test.ts src/agents/tools/media-generate-background-shared.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.session-lock.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `AUTOREVIEW_AUTO_TESTS=0 .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview`\n- `npm pack --silent --pack-destination /tmp/openclaw-local-proof-latest`\n- Installed `/tmp/openclaw-local-proof-latest/openclaw-2026.5.17.tgz` globally and restarted the local gateway.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Discord/Rosita image-to-video follow-up no longer starts another still-image generation for the same media completion flow. Completion delivery is confirmed before the media task is marked terminal, and failed delivery/provider runs do not poison the recent-success duplicate guard.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw gateway installed from this branch tarball, Discord server `Rosita`, channel `#general`, session `agent:main:discord:channel:1506010994416025762`, proof marker `PRPROOF-5384`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Installed packed tarball `fa880b2f38f7c8e0812ee14416e53f9f86ce65a619d82875e91839f30fac3167`, restarted gateway, sent one Discord image request for `PRPROOF-5384`, then sent image-to-video follow-up requests in the same Rosita `#general` session.\n\nEvidence after fix: Screenshot and task ledger artifact: https://gist.github.com/fuller-stack-dev/9e2e4f6752f142447bd59ec289dac424\n\n![Rosita #general proof](https://gist.githubusercontent.com/fuller-stack-dev/9e2e4f6752f142447bd59ec289dac424/raw/discord-prproof-5384-rosita-general-cropped.svg)\n\nObserved result after fix: The task ledger shows exactly one `image_generation` succeeded for `PRPROOF-5384`; the actual video tool retry succeeded as `video_generation` and delivered `video-1---61cb9662-4b01-490d-9844-d7531cac8e54.mp4` in Rosita `#general`. A prior xAI video attempt timed out, and the retry was allowed instead of being incorrectly blocked by stale duplicate state.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full repository check suite and non-Discord live channel paths were not run. The live proof covered the failing Discord/Rosita media-completion path directly.\n",
